<item>
            <title>[LU-14323] Interop: sanity-flr test 46 fails with &apos;Create /mnt/lustre/d46.sanity-flr/f46.sanity-flr failed&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14323</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity-flr test_46 fails for Lustre client version &amp;gt;=2.13.53.205 and Lustre server version &amp;lt; 2.13.53.205 and was added to Lustre by patch ee916af10de2 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13366&quot; title=&quot;SEL addons&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13366&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13366&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; utils: SEL yaml and copy file support). This test started failing for interop testing on 21 MAY 2020.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the suite_log for &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/dd663411-ee0e-4f68-bb37-4f8340ddac59&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/dd663411-ee0e-4f68-bb37-4f8340ddac59&lt;/a&gt;, the error looks like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity-flr test 46: Verify setstripe --copy option ================================================ 08:57:04 (1608800224)
  ** 1. PFL file
  ** 2. plain file
  ** 3. FLR file
  ** 4. PFL dir
  ** 5. plain dir
  ** 6. FLR dir
  ** 7. SEL file
lfs setstripe: cannot create composite file &apos;/mnt/lustre/d46.sanity-flr/f46.sanity-flr&apos;: Invalid argument
 sanity-flr test_46: @@@@@@ FAIL: Create /mnt/lustre/d46.sanity-flr/f46.sanity-flr failed 
  Trace dump:
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6273:error()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity-flr.sh:2103:test_46()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like skipping sanity-flr test 46 sub tests 7, 8, 9, and 10 should be skipped for Lustre server version &amp;gt;=2.13.53.205.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre client version &amp;gt;=2.13.53.205 and Lustre server version &amp;lt; 2.13.53.205 </environment>
